quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,61,"And [recall] when you said, "
  2,62,"Indeed, those who believed and those who were Jews or Christians or Sabeans [before Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ)] - those [among them] who believed in Allāh and the Last Day and did righteousness - will have their reward with their Lord, and no fear will there be concerning them, nor will they grieve{1}.",footnotes:1:After the coming of Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ) no religion other than Islām is acceptable to Allāh, as stated in 3:85.
  2,63,"And [recall] when We took your covenant, [O Children of Israel, to abide by the Torah] and We raised over you the mount, [saying], "
  3,1,"Alif, Lām, Meem.{1}",footnotes:1:See footnote to 2:1.
  3,2,"Allāh - there is no deity except Him, the Ever-Living, the Self-Sustaining.{1}",footnotes:1:See footnotes to 2:255.
  3,3,"He has sent down upon you, [O Muḥammad], the Book in truth, confirming what was before it. And He revealed the Torah and the Gospel"